text: Great n delicious Wu Xiang n far better than elsewhere in Bedok North like Blk 511 . Also great stall with sliced fish soup. Moved from town area hawker centre. The zhi zhar is also popular.

Tried the lor mee from this Noodle House. Uncle said he is from the Lor Ah Soo (now under Reno). Taste of old school. Next time will come for the laksa. For $4.50, the potion is big. Place very windy. Friendly service.
Except the curry fish, the rest of dishes were served cold, literally even below room temperature without any warm at all. Not so well.
Yummy fried prawn noodle (killer chilli, $5.5 (s)), 10x fried wontan $4.5

Food here includes the famous Lavendar Road Fish Soup stall, a nice WuXiang stall, great Sarawak Kolo Mee & Fried Hokkien Mee. Even the Zichar stall is pretty good. The place was well ventilated & breezy. Only minus was the smoking area whose smokers sharing of their cigarette smoke was urgghhh...spoilt the food taste.
